title: Tennis: Marchese earns win No. 600
text:
Ramapo girls tennis coach Kim Marchese, left, earned his 600th career victory Thursday. 
It also was coach Kim Marchese's 600th career win in girls tennis. 
Ramapo (13-3) defeated Demarest, 4-1, in the state sectional semifinals. 
Marchese is in his 32nd year as the Green Raiders' coach. 
Brianna Omar defeated Alina Chow, 6-2, 4-6, 6-1, in first singles, and Lauren Laino also needed three sets to beat Jesse Geller, 6-2, 4-6, 6-3, at third singles. Second-seeded Ramapo's doubles teams of Liz Kogan and Nicolette Kogut and Ella Sinoway and Jolie Straus swept their matches in straight sets. Demarest's Sabrina Jacobs earned its only point, defeating Taylor Thum, 5-7, 6-3, (10-1).
